From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shadow <shadow@code-puppy.dev>
Date: Fri, 04 Apr 2026 03:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix: prevent inplace reuse of INPUT-marked tensors in gallocr

The gallocr allocator checks GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_OUTPUT to prevent
inplace buffer reuse for output tensors, but does NOT check
GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_INPUT. This allows intermediate operations to
overwrite input buffers that are still needed later in the graph.

For MoE models, the argsort output (selected_experts / ffn_moe_topk)
is marked as INPUT via ggml_set_input() but its buffer gets reused
by downstream operations, corrupting expert IDs before MUL_MAT_ID
can read them. This causes GGML_ASSERT(id >= 0 && id < n_expert)
failures during expert copy.

Fix: Add GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_INPUT to the inplace reuse check alongside
the existing GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_OUTPUT check.

---
 ggml/src/ggml-alloc.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-alloc.c b/ggml/src/ggml-alloc.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/ggml/src/ggml-alloc.c
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-alloc.c
@@ -641,8 +641,8 @@ static void ggml_gallocr_allocate_node(struct ggml_gallocr * galloc, struct ggml
                     continue;
                 }

-                // outputs cannot be reused
-                if (parent->flags & GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_OUTPUT || (parent->view_src != NULL && parent->view_src->flags & GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_OUTPUT)) {
+                // outputs and inputs cannot be reused
+                if (parent->flags & (GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_OUTPUT | GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_INPUT) || (parent->view_src != NULL && parent->view_src->flags & (GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_OUTPUT | GGML_TENSOR_FLAG_INPUT))) {
                     AT_PRINTF("not reusing parent %s for %s as it is an output\n", parent->name, node->name);
                     continue;
                 }
